<li id="cite_note-WP-3">^ <a href="#cite_ref-WP_3-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WP_3-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WP_3-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WP_3-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WP_3-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WP_3-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREF.5B.5BHoward_Kurtz.5D.5D2006"><a href="/wiki/Howard_Kurtz" title="Howard Kurtz">Howard Kurtz</a> (2006-06-08). "<a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/blog/2006/06/08/BL2006060800389_3.html" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/blog/2006/06/08/BL2006060800389_3.html" rel="nofollow">Cats and Dogs Edition</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/The_Washington_Post" title="The Washington Post">The Washington Post</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/blog/2006/06/08/BL2006060800389_3.html" class="external free" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/blog/2006/06/08/BL2006060800389_3.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/blog/2006/06/08/BL2006060800389_3.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-05-04</span>.  "Mr. Ho called him 'uncle,' a familiar way of addressing an elder male in Cantonese."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Cats+and+Dogs+Edition&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BThe+Washington+Post%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BHoward+Kurtz%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BHoward+Kurtz%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2006-06-08&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-dyn%2Fcontent%2Fblog%2F2006%2F06%2F08%2FBL2006060800389_3.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Bus_Uncle"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Quotes from a <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wall_Street_Journal" title="The Wall Street Journal">Wall Street Journal</a></i> article.</li>
<li id="cite_note-SCMP1-4">^ <a href="#cite_ref-SCMP1_4-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SCMP1_4-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFLam2006">Lam, Agnes (2006-05-30). "Bus Uncle taught me a lesson: take a different bus". <i><a href="/wiki/South_China_Morning_Post" title="South China Morning Post">South China Morning Post</a></i>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Bus+Uncle+taught+me+a+lesson%3A+take+a+different+bus&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BSouth+China+Morning+Post%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Lam&amp;rft.aufirst=Agnes&amp;rft.au=Lam%2C+Agnes&amp;rft.date=2006-05-30&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Bus_Uncle"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
